1+11+111+\cdots+\underbrace{11\ldots1}_{n}
1=\frac{10-1}{9}=\frac{10^1-1}{9}
11=\frac{100-1}{9}=\frac{10^2-1}{9}
111=\frac{1000-1}{9}=\frac{10^3-1}{9}
\underbrace{11\ldots1}_{n}=\frac{10^n-1}{9}
\begin{align*}1+11+111+\cdot\cdot\cdot+\underbrace{111...1}_{n}&=\frac{10^1-1}{9}+\frac{10^2-1}{9}+\frac{10^3-1}{9}+\cdot\cdot\cdot+\frac{10^n-1}{9}\\ &=\frac{10}{9}-\frac{1}{9}+\frac{10^2}{9}-\frac{1}{9}+\frac{10^3}{9}-\frac{1}{9}+\cdot\cdot\cdot+\frac{10^n}{9}-\frac{1}{9}\\  &=\frac{10}{9}+\frac{10^2}{9}+\frac{10^3}{9}+\cdot\cdot\cdot+\frac{10^n}{9}-(\frac{1}{9}+\frac{1}{9}+\frac{1}{9}\cdot\cdot\cdot+\frac{1}{9})\\&=\frac{10}{9}(1+10+10^2+\cdot\cdot\cdot+10^{n-1})-\frac{1}{9}(1+1+1+\cdot\cdot\cdot+1)\\&=\frac{10}{9}\cdot \frac{10^n-1}{9}-\frac{1}{9}\cdot n=\frac{10}{81}(10^n-1)-\frac{n}{9}.\end{align*}
\underbrace{11\ldots1}_n=\dfrac{10^n-1}9
\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{10^n-1}9 = \frac19\sum_{k=1}^n10^k-\frac n9=\frac19\cdot \frac{10^{n+1}-10}9-\frac n9.
